A 29-year-old man was fatally stabbed in broad daylight when a fight broke out during a soccer game in Upper Manhattan. Ricardo Sanchez was playing soccer inside Fort Washington Park at West 165th Street and Riverside Drive just before 4 p.m. Sunday when acquaintance Ronald Guilcapi, 24, repeatedly stabbed him with a broken bottle during a scuffle, police said. Sanchez of Bedford-Stuyvesant, Brooklyn, was taken to Mount Sinai Morningside, where he was pronounced dead. He had suffered stab wounds to the chest, arm and neck, cops said. Guilicapi, 24, who lives just under a mile from the scene, was arrested and charged with murder, police said. The circumstances leading up to the deadly clash remained unknown Monday afternoon.